EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 192300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO LIE
OVER THE ICELAND AREA WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE 1002 WITH A
WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LYING FM BISCAY NE ACROSS
EERN PARTS OF THE BRITISH ISLES AND INTO THE N SEA.
DURING FRIDAY AND SATURDAY A NEW ATLANTIC LOW WILL MOV
NWARDS TO LIE TO THE S OF ICELAND WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE
1000 BY MIDDAY ON SATURDAY. THIS LOW THEN BECOMES SLOW-
MOV AND SLWY FILLS TO 1007 BY SUNDAY EVENING. A RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO PERSIST THROUGH FRIDAY AND
SATURDAY FM THE AZORES NE ACROSS THE S OF THE BRITISH
ISLES AND INTO THE N SEA BEFORE DECLINING DURING SUNDAY.
WINDS ARE EXP TO REMAIN GENERALLY LIGHT ACROSS THE WHOLE
OF THE CULLERCOATS REGION THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD WITH
